rd for bot, which only works if cloudflared is running on your server. If it’s not running, Cloudflare shows 502 Host error. ✅ If you want Cloudflare Pages Do this in Cloudflare DNS: Delete the existing bot Tunnel record. Create a CNAME: Name: bot Target: YOUR-PROJECT.pages.dev (your Pages domain) Proxy: ✅ Proxied (orange cloud) Then in Pages → Settings → Environment Variables, set: VITE_API_BASE_URL = your backend URL (example: https://api.insightprofit.live) VITE_OAUTH_PORTAL_URL and VITE_APP_ID (if used) ✅ If you want Cloudflare Tunnel Then you MUST have cloudflared running 24/7 on your server. Please open a terminal on the server and run: Copy cloudflared tunnel list If it shows no running tunnel, that is the cause of 502. Tell me which one you want: Pages or Tunnel Once you answer, I’ll give you the exact clicks to fix it. i want all the subdomains always working and running no matter the device or browser and hace my content saved and availabel to keep working. whicih is th eoptimal setup. For “always working on any device/browser” with saved content, the optimal setup is: ✅ Recommended (Most Reliable) Cloudflare Tunnel + VPS + Docker + Persistent Volumes Why: Cloudflare Tunnel keeps your services online without exposing your server IP. Docker runs your apps reliably. Persistent volumes keep your data safe between restarts. Works on any device/browser with HTTPS. How it works One VPS/server (always on) Docker Compose for all apps (bot, supabase, etc.) Cloudflare Tunnel with public hostnames: bot.insightprofit.live → your bot container supabase.insightprofit.live → supabase container etc. This is the most stable “always on” setup. ✅ Alternative (Only for static websites) Cloudflare Pages Great for static frontend only. Cannot run your Node server or database. You would still need a backend host separately. Next step (you choose) Tell me which you want to standardize on: A) Cloudflare Tunnel (recommended for always‑on + data saved) B) Cloudflare Pages (static only) Once you pick, I’ll give you exact step‑by‑step instructions (no coding). all my projects are interactive websites. do not run as if static Understood. Since all your projects are interactive, the correct setup is: ✅ Cloudflare Tunne"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"[Content truncated — view full chat at source URL]"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"Source: "},{"type":"link","href":"https://www.genspark.ai/agents?id=d807e424-78b5-4aff-a8ba-6df6f16f7b7e","children":[{"text":"https://www.genspark.ai/agents?id=d807e424-78b5-4aff-a8ba-6df6f16f7b7e"}]}]}]
